## Anti-Patterns (NEVER DO)

### Error Handling Anti-Patterns
- **NEVER** use generic error messages
- **NEVER** return raw database errors to clients
- **NEVER** use panic() in production code
- **NEVER** ignore errors
- **ALWAYS** use structured error handling

### Security in Error Handling
- **NEVER** expose internal errors to clients
- **ALWAYS** log detailed errors internally
- **ALWAYS** return generic error messages to clients
- **ALWAYS** use proper HTTP status codes

## Error Handling Checklist
- [ ] All errors are properly wrapped with context
- [ ] No raw database errors exposed to clients
- [ ] Proper HTTP status codes used
- [ ] Internal errors logged with details
- [ ] Client errors are generic and safe